I’m at a point in my life where my belief in myself & God has never been stronger. A lot of people have ideas about what they think I should be doing and I don’t blame them - It’s safer and involves less risk. 

But here’s the thing. This journey It’s not about absolutes. It’s not about whether it works out or it doesn’t work out.

If it’s one thing I realized in 2022, it’s that I have options and I owe it to myself to see what they are. I can’t allow other peoples energies to sway me. 

I trust that the decisions in making are going to lead me to where I want to be. Doesn’t mean there will never be struggles or I’ll never need help - but it does mean that I followed my heart & trusted myself to take me along this unpredictable journey. 🫶🏽

Everything is working out for me 🥂

I’m on the verge of a breakthrough - I can almost touch it. ✨ It’s exciting, confusing and honestly a bit lonely. 

I have been shedding the old parts of myself for awhile now & it’s finally at the tail end. 

My relationships have changed. Majority of my friendships feel very different than before + I’m not close with a lot of people anymore. I’m actually not sure if I ever was because I’ve had a bad habit of making an encounter mean more than it really does. 

Once I realized that it takes 2, I stopped putting in enormous effort and correctly managed my investment and energy to where there is no resentment or disappointment present. I am fully accepting that things that were, no longer are and that’s okay. I appreciate the temporary alignment that occurred and am looking forward to meeting my soul tribe. 🤍

On another note, God is telling me that it’s time. And I know a lot of you feel this way in your life, too. Spring is here & there are rebirths happening all around us. 

Lean into it. 

It’s time to show up in the way you’ve been dreaming of. It’s time to push past the doubt and finally poke a big hole in it. It’s time to put daily intentional effort into co-creating the life that you desire. It’s time to focus and stand 10 toes down. 

Remember: discomfort is only TEMPORARY. Let this season stretch you, challenge you and disrupt your limiting beliefs because our time is very close. 

We’ve rested enough. Time to turn it up a notch! 

I saw a quote recently that said “there’s not much you need to change, but there’s a lot you need to embody” and WOW. What will you be embodying for this new chapter of your life? 👇🏽

Best date night goes to @juliet.htx 🤍 Here are my full thoughts:

OVERALL EXPERIENCE: 10/10 

🍸 DRINKS RATING: The drinks were a 10/10. I know when a cocktail is made horribly w/ little effort. I had zero complaints with the Strawberry Lemon Drop & “The Kiss”. The girlies been onto something!! I peeped the drinks were like $20 - I wasn’t paying anyway duh - and they were worth every dime! 

🍽️ FOOD RATING: 9/10. For main starters: Calamari & Thai Chile Shrimp. For the entree: Lamb Rack w/ Wine sauce w/ Mac & cheese (very popular) & Brussels sprouts as the side. The lamb was perfect! I didn’t really care for the wine sauce but I think it’s great to have on the side. 

📝 OTHER NOTES: I did go on a weekday night so we were able to sit in a booth vs. a table for two. So when you book your reservation, keep in mind that the traffic & atmosphere is gonna shift depending on the day. 

Overall, I had a really really good time and left a very happy happy girl! My best date yet 🙊 Let me know if you end up going here ❤️

There’s so many reasons why it seems like you can’t do the thing. And there’s 100 more reasons why you can. 

It’s okay to be afraid. 

The presence of fear doesn’t mean you shouldn’t pursue it. It simply means your fears have a message for you. You’re afraid. So what! Acknowledgment is the first step!! 

For me, I’ve been afraid of being seen because I honestly didn’t know what being seen felt like or looked like. What I’ve come to learn is that in order to be received, you must be seen & in order to be seen, you must share yourself with the world.

Scary shit, right? I know. & guess what? You’re still more than capable of starting. A little bit of trouble shooting is normal but how will you know what you’re capable of if you don’t TRULY try? 

Be open.
Be willing. 
Be committed.

It’s time to go. do. the. thing. bestie🤍 what dream/idea was nagging at you as you read the caption? 👇🏽

I am so deeply grateful for God’s continuous guidance to allow my most authentic self to shine. 26 felt like my first *actual* year in adulthood and baby, I was fighting for my life the whole first half. The second half showed me that no matter where you start, there’s always a possibility for change. 

27 is about risking it all. Everything I want, I’m allowing myself to try. I’ve always been a dreamer and this year I’m turning those dreams into something tangible.

I’m no longer hiding in the shadows. My wildest dreams can’t come true there. 

Although my heart still aches for what what was, the hope I have cannot be moved, shaken nor taken from me. There is so much goodness ahead of me and I’m prepared to bask in it.

Thank you so much for receiving my art & riding with me on this unpredictable journey to authenticity. Cheers to 27 🥂🤍

One thing I notice every year around my birthday is how my community has changed and evolved. Although this post is about enjoying my own company (AND DIDDDD) here’s a brain dump of what’s been on my mind 🧠

Moving away from home twice to new states is HARD. Having to build your community from the ground up takes time and it has definitely left me feeling lonely a lot of times. You see everyone’s life continuing to go on and at times, almost feel isolated and forgotten because you’re no longer a part of that community. People will even visit here & I don’t hear from em & in that moment I realize, OH shit - we’ve shifted to acquaintances so why should I expect that? 

It also sucks bc it’s not like I haven’t tried to expand it, you know? I go work alone, workout alone, work towards my goals alone + eat alone majority of the time. Sometimes I question if I’m even gonna meet my community in Houston or maybe it’s the next city I go to. 

My closest friends live so far and I feel grief because I’m not physically there to see them evolve in their unique ways and spend time with them 🥹

So do I love my own company? Absolutely. And I’m also looking forward to the day where I’m physically surrounded around people that truly know me and make an effort to stay in my life.

Anyway, that’s just how I’ve been feeling. Growing pains, maybe? I pray my tribe finds me in perfect timing. Not forcing anything at all + will continue to keep my heart open. 🤍

Sending love to anyone that resonates!

Well. 🤭 that day has come! I’m SOOOO excited to be introducing you to my new baby: @returntobloomcounseling 🤍

I’m an entrepreneur at heart yet there’s so much responsibility that comes with it and I was tryna escape it at every turn.

Scared of failure.
Scared of success.
Scared of responsibility.

God recently pulled me out of environments that simply weren’t for me which prompted me to start my own therapy private practice. I couldn’t help people the way I wanted to and the right people had trouble finding me. No matter what place I worked at, it literally did NOT work out. The most recent ending made me realize it was time I started fully trusting in the path God was creating for me. 

I knew this was in my future but I never would’ve thought it would happen so soon! I was born to help people heal. That’s a fact. But I’m not for everyone. The people I am for, leave my presence being deeply touched and it’s a true honor to be a vessel. 

To the Keionna who felt deeply misunderstood, we did it! You have nothing to prove to anyone.

@returntobloomcounseling is a place where you return to your most authentic self, & bloom into your highest self. ✨ HUGE s/o to @ashmamafit_ for helping me with the name.

The aftermath of being diagnosed with PCOS was confusing because I still didn’t understand exactly what was happening in my body. I knew the SYMPTOMS but I was missing how they developed. I had to do a lot of research on insulin resistance, fiber intake + protein intake. What’s most frustrating is that doctors will just tell you to lose weight but fail to tailor their advice to the condition you have. 

All the research to start something or work towards a goal can be OVERWHELMING. So ordering this walking pad was my first foot forward to managing my PCOS. 
I do enjoy walking, but not in the cold. Getting a walking pad will make meeting that goal a lot easier. 

Meeting yourself where you’re at looks like knowing what isn’t gonna work and also challenging yourself! I’m looking forward to see my progress along with strength training, pilates and yoga. 🧘🏽‍♀️

It’s officially been 2 months in business and I sit in gratitude. After my session & consultation today, I’ll have completed 35 sessions. Some of my clients have graduated from weekly to biweekly because of their commitment 🥺 

Last weekend I held my first healing circle & the impact was substantial. Naturally, we reflected on 2023 and I realized I needed to sit with my own growth just as much as I was encouraging others to. 

This ain’t my first rodeo but it definitely hits different. Here’s some random advice if you have a dream:

💌 Get away from people who don’t believe in you. Idc who it is, you don’t need that energy in your space. Empowerment & genuine support only! 

💌 Commit to the vision AND be flexible. Things may not turn out EXACTLY how you want because there are 1,000 ways to reach one goal but as long as you reach the goal - that’s what matters. 

💌 Sometimes you gotta leave an environment to see growth. If you know in your spirit it’s not for you, trust yourself and leave. Sometimes it’s not a no, but a not here. 

💌 Pop yo shit. Don’t be shy about what you do, what service you offer & what impact you can have in people’s lives. The ones that want to receive that, will find you.

I believe in you bestie & 2024 has lots in store for both of us. 🤍 
What’s 1 thing you accomplished this year that you’re proud of? POP YO SHITTTT!
